    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>End Oil and Gas Tax Subsidies Act of 2015</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to: </p> <ul> <li>increase to seven years the amortization period for geological and geophysical expenditures; </li> <li>repeal the tax credits for producing oil and gas from marginal wells and for enhanced oil recovery;</li> <li>repeal the tax deduction for the intangible drilling and development costs of oil and gas wells; </li> <li>repeal percentage depletion for oil and gas wells;</li> <li>repeal the tax deduction for tertiary injectant expenses; </li> <li>repeal the passive loss exception for working interests in oil and gas property; </li> <li>deny the tax deduction for income attributable to domestic production activities for oil and gas activities; </li> <li>prohibit the use of the last-in, first-out (LIFO) accounting method by major integrated oil companies; and </li> <li>limit the foreign tax credit for dual capacity taxpayers (i.e., taxpayers who are subject to a levy of a foreign country or U.S. possession and receive specific economic benefits from such country or possession). </li> </ul>]]></text>
